The parfu tool was developed as part of the Blue Waters sustained-petascale computing project, which is supported by the National Science Foundation (awards OCI-0725070 and ACI-1238993) and the state of Illinois. Blue Waters is a joint effort of the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign and its National Center for Supercomputing Applications.

The author thanks Greg Bauer, head of the Blue Waters SEAS team for supporting this project.  
The author also thanks Bill Kramer and the Blue Waters project in general for their support and their authorization for the release of this tool.
